post_text:
The Durham Place is the home and doctor's office/apothecary used by the Durham doctors of Maxeys and the surrounding area. They were well known in the 18th and early 19th centuries as accomplished doctors who used a variety of medical methods (including herbal remedies that they developed and prepared themselves) to treat patients. Durham Apothecary also gives tribute to Dr. Lindsey Durham of Scull Shoals fame.

The Durham Place was added to the National Register of Historic Places in 2017.

The Durham Apothecary and Museum is open Thursday, Friday, and Saturday 8am ‚Äì 3pm. Stop by to visit soon!

post_text:
The Gillen House Bed and Breakfast is now open in Maxeys. The house was originally built in 1920 by Andrew J. Gillen, Jr. Gillen Jr. was born in Maxeys in 1862 to Irish immigrant Andrew Gillen Sr and Elizbeth Tuggle Gillen. Gillen Jr established The Gillen Department Store, as well as serving several years on the county Board of Education.

The Gillen House Bed and Breakfast owner‚Äôs Edward Toledano and Cynzia Sanchez purchased the house and began a full renovation in August 2018. In addition to the newly renovated house, the property consists of two acres of grounds including a pecan orchard, vegetable and herb garden, koi pond and golf putting green.

The owners are hosting an Open House Tour on Sunday, May 19th from 2pm-5pm.

Please see the linked featured article from the Athens Banner-Herald on the new bed and breakfast in the May 12th Sunday paper.

post_text:
Oglethorpe County has a long history of BBQ. Sanders‚Äô Down Home Barbeque & Soul Food in Vesta community is part of it. Founded in 2011 when family patriarch Carlton Sanders returned home to Vesta after retiring from a large tobacco company in Atlanta.

Mr. Sanders got his start in BBQ restaurants in 1955 in Atlanta when he would take a bus from Oglethorpe County every weekend to work in a BBQ restaurant there.

Sanders BBQ is a family run business with Carlton and son Steve along with other members of the Sanders family. They specialize in sliced pork BBQ, chicken, ribs, and soul food. Their made to order lemon pepper pork rinds are worth the trip alone.

Sanders BBQ was closed the last two weekends for upgrades done to the building and kitchen area, but they are back to their regular hours Labor Day Weekend.

Check out this Oglethorpe County treasure Friday and Saturdays ‚Äì 10am - 8pm. They are located at 3078 Elberton Rd., Carlton, GA 30627. Cash only.

#DiscoverOglethorpe
